		{"id":"extracted_metrics","type":"text","text":"## 📊 EXTRACTED METRICS\n\n**Basic Statistics**\n• Total nodes: 47\n• Total edges: 34\n• Text nodes: 47\n• Large texts (>500 chars): 10\n• Missing data alerts: 2\n• Unique concepts: 23\n\n**Theory Structure**\n• 11 Laws of Physics\n• 12 Quarks/Continents\n• 96 Hadrons\n• 384 Sub-hadrons\n  ├─ 342 Possible (89.1%)\n  └─ 42 Impossible (10.9%)\n\n**Mathematical Properties**\n• 10.9% constant (antimatter)\n• 4 fundamental forces\n• 11 ontological laws\n• 32 × 4 × 6 × 5 = 384\n\n**Validation Results**\n• Tested on 28 repos\n• Comprehension: 4.2h → 6.8m (-97.3%)\n• Graph size: 12k → 214 nodes (-98.2%)\n• CQRS detection: 100%","x":2000,"y":-2000,"width":350,"height":400},

		{"id":"four_forces","type":"text","text":"## ⚛️ THE FOUR FORCES\n\n| Force | Intensity | Software Dimension | Values |\n|-------|-----------|-------------------|---------|\n| Strong | 10³⁸ | Responsibility (Domain) | Create, Update, Delete, FindById, Compensate, Project… (32) |\n| Electromagnetic | 10³⁶ | Purity (side-effects) | Pure, Impure, Idempotent, ExternalIO (4) |\n| Weak | 10²⁵ | Boundary (layer) | Domain, Application, Infra, Adapter, API, Test (6) |\n| Gravity | 10⁰ | Lifecycle (temporal) | Singleton, Scoped, Transient, Ephemeral, Immortal (5) |\n\n**Mathematical relationship**\n32 × 4 × 7 × 5 = 4480 → filtered → 384 → 42 impossible → 342 possible\n\n**Conservation laws**\n• Domain intention conservation\n• Referential transparency\n• Dependency inversion\n• Memory lifecycle","x":2400,"y":-2000,"width":400,"height":350},

		{"id":"impossible_patterns","type":"text","text":"## 🚫 42 IMPOSSIBLE PATTERNS\n\n**Architectural Antimatter**\n\n1. CommandHandler::FindById (CQRS violation)\n2. QueryHandler::Save (CQRS violation)\n3. Entity::Stateless (identity contradiction)\n4. ValueObject::HasIdentity (value contradiction)\n5. RepositoryImpl::PureFunction (I/O contradiction)\n6. PureFunction::ExternalIO (purity violation)\n7. EventHandler::ReturnsValue (fire-and-forget)\n8. TestFunction::ModifiesProductionData\n9. APIHandler::InternalOnly (boundary violation)\n10. Service::GlobalState (DDD violation)\n11. AggregateRoot::NoInvariants\n12. Validator::AcceptsInvalid\n13. Middleware::SkipsNext\n14. HealthCheck::Returns500WhenHealthy\n15. GracefulShutdown::HardKill\n... + 27 more\n\n**Visualization**: Black holes with red pulsing halos","x":2850,"y":-2000,"width":350,"height":450},

		{"id":"data_atoms","type":"text","text":"## 🧬 DATA ATOMS HIERARCHY\n\n1. **Bits** - Fundamental unit\n2. **Bytes** - 8 bits\n3. **Primitives** - int, float, string\n4. **Variables** - Named storage\n5. **Expressions** - Combinations\n6. **Statements** - Complete instructions\n7. **Control Structures** - if, for, while\n8. **Functions** - Reusable blocks\n9. **Aggregates** - Collections\n10. **Modules** - Function groups\n11. **Files** - Persistent storage\n12. **Executables** - Running code\n\n**Foundation Layers**\n• Data Foundations (Bits → Variables)\n• Logic & Flow (Expressions → Functions)\n• Organization (Aggregates → Files)\n• Execution (Executables)","x":3250,"y":-2000,"width":300,"height":450},

		{"id":"spectrometer_v10","type":"text","text":"## 🔬 SPECTROMETER v10\n\n**Core Capabilities**\n• AST parsing (LibCST/Tree-sitter)\n• Symbolic graph construction\n• 96 + 11 ontological rules\n• 342 pattern classification\n• 42 impossible detection\n\n**Process Flow**\n1. Parse AST with comments\n2. Build symbol table & scope\n3. Apply ontological rules\n4. Classify nodes (342 possible)\n5. Detect violations (42 impossible)\n6. Generate reduced graph\n\n**Performance**\n• 10k-120k LOC supported\n• 5 languages tested\n• <3s for CQRS violations\n• 6.8 min comprehension time\n\n**Output**: Reduced graph + valence report + black holes","x":2000,"y":-1500,"width":350,"height":400},

		{"id":"quantum_extensions","type":"text","text","## 🌀 QUANTUM EXTENSIONS\n\n**Advanced Concepts**\n• Entanglement - Cross-component dependencies\n• Wave Collapse - Pattern resolution at runtime\n• Quantum Fluctuations - Probabilistic matching\n• Spectral Oscillations - Frequency analysis\n\n**Visual Effects**\n• Glowing particles for rare patterns\n• Pulsating halos for quantum states\n• Wave interference for conflicts\n• Tunnels for deep dependencies\n\n**Theoretical Support**\nThe Standard Model supports quantum behavior in:\n• Superposition of responsibilities\n• Entangled lifecycles\n• Quantum purity states\n• Boundary tunneling","x":2400,"y":-1500,"width":350,"height":350},

		{"id":"missing_sources","type":"text","text":"## ⚠️ MISSING SOURCES\n\n**Required Data**\n1. **96 Hadrons**\n   - Need source CSV/List\n   - Pattern definitions\n   - Relationship mappings\n\n2. **384 Sub-hadrons**\n   - Complete enumeration\n   - Impossible pattern list\n   - Frequency statistics\n\n**Next Steps**\n• Source original research data\n• Validate theoretical patterns\n• Compile statistical frequency\n• Create visual mappings\n\n**Impact**: Without these sources, the model remains theoretical without empirical validation.","x":2850,"y":-1500,"width":350,"height":350},

		{"id":"key_insights","type":"text","text":"## 💡 KEY INSIGHTS\n\n1. **Predictive Power**\n   - Can predict patterns before implementation\n   - Slot-based system (384 total slots)\n   - Empty slots indicate future patterns\n\n2. **Rarity Detection**\n   - <1% frequency = exotic architecture\n   - 0.1% frequency = potential smell\n   - 0% frequency = impossible (42 patterns)\n\n3. **Universal Constants**\n   - 10.9% antimatter across systems\n   - 4 fundamental forces hierarchy\n   - 11 ontological laws\n\n4. **Practical Impact**\n   - 97.3% faster comprehension\n   - 98.2% smaller graphs\n   - 100% violation detection\n\n5. **Cross-Domain Mapping**\n   - Same constants in OKLCH color space\n   - Chemical elements analogy\n   - Physics force mapping","x":3250,"y":-1500,"width":350,"height":400}
